  "doc_id": "1738",
  "text": "Several authors have carried out computational simulations of entrance flows [5 -9] . Luo and Mitsoulis [CITATION_1] showed that LDPE and HDPE behave differently mainly because of the elongational viscosity, which is substantially strainhardening for the LDPE but strain-thinning for the HDPE melt. For creeping flow of a LDPE melt Mitsoulis [CITATION_2] has demonstrated that the size of the corner vortex grows monotonically with apparent shear rate up to about 40 s -1 , after which it remains constant before starting to diminish above apparent shear rate of 100 s -1 .",
